headlines.description: — Kelly Oubre Jr. scored 28 points, and the Charlotte Hornets stopped Minnesota's five-game win streak with a 110-108 victory over Anthony Edwards and the Timberwolves on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oubre scores 28, Hornets snap T-Wolves' 5-game win streak

headlines.description: — Shake Milton had 24 points, a career-high 10 assists and nine rebounds, and the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers beat the Orlando Magic 107-99 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shake Milton helps short-handed 76ers beat Magic 107-99

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jerami Grant scored a career-high 44 points, Anfernee Simons had 38 and the Portland Trail Blazers outlasted the New York Knicks 132-129 in overtime on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jerami Grant scores 44, Blazers beat Knicks 132-129 in OT

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 30 points and the NBA-best Boston Celtics pulled away from the Sacramento Kings for a 122-104 victory on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 30; Celtics pull away from Kings, 122-104

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield scored 26 points to lead four Indiana players with 20 or more, and the Pacers beat the Brooklyn Nets 128-117 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers have 4 players with 20-plus points, beat Nets 128-117

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo scored a season-high 38 points and the Miami Heat beat the Washington Wizards 110-107 Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo scores 38 points to lead Heat past Wizards

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 30 points, Kenyon Martin Jr. and rookie Jabari Smith Jr. added 21 each and the Houston Rockets overcame a 15-point second half deficit to beat the Atlanta Hawks 128-122 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green has 30 points, Rockets rally to beat Hawks 128-122

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Dillon Brooks scored 25 points, Ja Morant had 23 points and 11 assists as the Memphis Grizzlies built an early lead on 3-point shooting and routed the New Orleans Pelicans 132-111 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brooks, Morant lead Grizzlies in rout of Pelicans, 132-111

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo and the Milwaukee Bucks taught the Cleveland Cavaliers a lesson in playoff-type intensity well before the start of December.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks storm back in 2nd half to beat Cavaliers 117-102

events.name: Chicago Bulls at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 30 points, including five straight free throws in the final minute of overtime, and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Chicago Bulls 123-119 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander stars as Thunder beat Bulls 123-119 in OT

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — LeBron James’ return from a five-game absence helped push the Los Angeles Lakers to their first road victory of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lakers top Spurs in James' return for first road victory

headlines.description: — Cameron Payne drove into the lane with a minute remaining in the game and tossed a short jumper toward the rim. Detroit's Marvin Bagley III immediately swatted the shot back into Payne's face.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ayton, Booker lead Suns to 108-102 win over Pistons

events.name: Utah Jazz at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — As Klay Thompson stays patient searching for his shot, the Golden State Warriors' offense starts humming along like days of old.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 33 points as Warriors beat Jazz 129-118

headlines.description: — Denver coach Michael Malone knew when the schedule came out that his team was going to have to be successful again on the road if it was going to be contend in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gordon scores 29, Nuggets beat short-handed Clippers 114-104
